comment.narrative:
Component 1: To achieve sustainable development goals on ensuring sound management of chemicals the project conducted an analysis of the policy and measures of chemicals management and implementation of chemical conventions in Kazakhstan. They are:
–	report on the problems, shortcomings and barriers to national legislation for the coordinated implementation of all chemical conventions with consideration of gender aspects in chemical management was prepared;
–	the draft of National Profile on chemicals management. Capacity building on chemicals and waste issues;
–	recommendations for a coordination mechanism for chemicals management prepared
–	proposals for Improving Legal Mechanisms for Chemicals Management were prepared and submitted to Government; 
–	proposals have been prepared on the harmonization of legislation in the field of public health, environmental protection, safety of chemical products, labor protection, industrial safety; 
–	proposals on strengthening the chemicals regulation in consumer goods were prepared;
–	analysis of export and import of chemicals; 
–	analysis of production and use of chemical substances was carried out.
–	A draft National Profile on chemicals management was prepared.

Component 2: 
Legislative proposals were discussed with representatives of government agencies, associations, NGOs, industrial enterprises at the Inception workshop. Taking into account these recommendations, the proposals were updated and presented at the webinar “Management of industrial and hazardous waste, chemicals in the draft of the new Environmental Code of the Republic of Kazakhstan”, online conference “Requirements and recommendations for handling industrial chemicals and hazardous waste”, online seminar training on legislation and the approval of the report on the problems, shortcomings and obstacles to national legislation. A round table was held on the coordination of chemical conventions. A meeting of the working group was held: Discussion of the mechanism of intersectoral coordination of issues of handling chemicals. 



Component 4.
Building capacity of medical personnel and establishment of sustainable healthcare waste management system under COVID-19 conditions
-Purchased of equipment to dispose of infected medical waste, instlatted in CSE on the REM «City Center of Phthisiopulmonology » of Nur-Sultan Akimate
-Prepared review on international experience; 
-Prepared analysis of the current regulatory legal acts;
-Prepared standards for healthcare waste generation  
-Developed general guidance for the disposal of liquid medical waste
-Developed Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for healthcare waste treatment
-Developed training, including online one for employees of medical institutions on the collection, sorting, transportation of waste 
-Developed information and methodology for target groups (representatives of state bodies, medical institutions, enterprises for the disposal of healthcare waste, population, NGOs)
-Conducted training for trainers of medical workers
